@startuml
title Viaverse Notification / Delivery State — State Diagram

[*] --> CREATED
CREATED --> SUPPRESSED : policy/no consent
CREATED --> QUEUED : notify
QUEUED --> SCHEDULED : quiet hours/digest
SCHEDULED --> QUEUED : time reached
QUEUED --> DISPATCHING : send attempt
DISPATCHING --> SENT : provider success
DISPATCHING --> FAILED : provider failure
FAILED --> SCHEDULED : retry/backoff
SENT --> READ : user opens
SENT --> ARCHIVED : user archives
READ --> ARCHIVED : archive

SUPPRESSED --> [*]
ARCHIVED --> [*]

note bottom
Inbox item and delivery attempts can have separate states.
SENT means at least one selected delivery channel succeeded,
not necessarily read.
end note
@enduml
